{"questionId":"27632","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi></math> be a constant, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award a maximum of <em><strong>M1A0A0</strong></em> if the candidate manipulates both sides of the equation (such as moving terms from one side to the other).</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 1 (working with LHS)</strong></p>\n<p>attempting to expand&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;(do not accept&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>LHS</mtext><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; or&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>RHS</mtext></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award the final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if further working contradicts the <em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2 (working with RHS)</strong></p>\n<p>attempting to expand&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mfenced><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>RHS</mtext><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>4</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>4</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi>a</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mtext>LHS</mtext></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></em><em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong>&nbsp;Do not award the final&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em>&nbsp;if further working contradicts the&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27632","referenceCode":"22N.1.SL.TZ0.4a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that a2+a2-122=a2+122.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.6—Simple proof"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}